[SN]TITLE[SN]
Miles Addison: Peterborough United defender extends deal

[SN]FIRST-SENTENCE[SN]
Peterborough United defender Miles Addison has signed a new one-month contract with the League One side.

[SN]RESTBODY[SN]
The 26-year-old has made just one appearance since joining Posh in November, scoring in the 3-2 win over former club Barnsley.
Graham Westley's side currently have injuries to fellow defenders Callum Elder, Gabriel Zakuani and Kgosi Ntlhe.
Posh, currently sixth in the table, are at home against struggling Chesterfield on Boxing Day.
